text: This is the old KTM railway track which is now converted to a walking / cycling path. Itâ€™s a great place to go for walks or cycling in middle of urban singapore as both sides are covered by trees and see various kinds of animals and insects . It also has markers every 100 m for those who want to see how far they have travelled along the path . Weekends can be busy .
Watch out for speeding bicycles and wear some reflective clothing or carry a torch at night. Avoid the corridor when it is raining.
